PrecisApproval of the appointment by the Minister of Supply and Services of certain persons as directors of the Board of Directors of the Royal Canadian Mint to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years. (Charles F.M. Ross, London, Ontario, in the place of Ken Boshcoff, whose term has expired; and Diane Marleau, Montreal, Quebec, in the place of Marc Bruneau, whose term has expired)
